1. Installation
Install dev dependency: npm install --save-dev vitest
Add npm scripts: "test": "vitest --run" and "test:watch": "vitest"

2. Test file conventions
By default Vitest recognizes files matching patterns: **/*.{test,spec}.{js,mjs,cjs,ts,mts,cts,jsx,tsx} or tests/ directory depending on config.

3. Core API
- describe(name, fn): group tests
- it(name, fn) / test(name, fn): individual test
- beforeEach(fn), afterEach(fn), beforeAll(fn), afterAll(fn): hooks
- expect(value): assertion entry

4. Matchers
Common matchers: toBe, toEqual, toStrictEqual, toContain, toHaveLength, toMatch, toThrow, resolves/rejects helpers for promises.
Examples: expect(sum(1,2)).toBe(3)

5. Configuration
vitest.config.js export default defineConfig({ test: { globals: true, environment: 'node'|'jsdom', setupFiles: ['./test/setup.js'] } })
Options: globals (boolean), environment (node or jsdom), test timeout, reporters, coverage provider configuration.

6. CLI and runner flags
- npx vitest or npm run test
- --run : run tests once (CI)
- --watch : run in watch mode
- --coverage : collect coverage
- --reporter <name> : select reporter

7. Coverage and CI
Use --coverage or enable coverage in config. Integrate with CI by running npx vitest --run --coverage and publishing coverage artifacts.

